**Solution 1: handle exception in getter**
&lt;br&gt;One approach that can be used is to modify your getter method using static methods: [Hibernate.isInitialized][1] and [Hibernate.initialize][2] and handle `EntityNotFoundException` 
```java
    public School getSchool() {
        if (!Hibernate.isInitialized(school)) {
            try {
                Hibernate.initialize(school);
            } catch (EntityNotFoundException ex) {
                school = null;
            }
        }
        return school;
    }
```
```java
